There is a very horrifying form of paranoia, when you feel responsible for everything that goes wrong in the world.

Through my improper posture, asymmetric breathing, ugly thoughts - I have caused trees to die, turned castles into ruin, and infected souls with rot. I am rabid.

But this is a lie - the mystery of the divine randomness, of lawlessness, continues to spread.

By crossing a street and making a car stop, you have secretly prevented a car crash. With every step you save hundreds of lives. With every tear, you make a forest blossom. Sun shines.
